《'''活摘'''》 （{{lang-en|'''''Human Harvest'''''}}）又名《'''大衛戰紅魔'''》（{{lang-en|'''''Davids and Goliath'''''}}）<ref>{{cite news |title=Davids and Goliath – Exposing One of the World’s Worst Crimes Against Humanity |url=https://theindiefest.com/success-stories/davids-and-goliath-exposing-one-of-the-worlds-worst-crimes-against-humanity/ |accessdate=2021-11-18 |work=theindiefest.com |archive-date=2021-11-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211118033858/https://theindiefest.com/success-stories/davids-and-goliath-exposing-one-of-the-worlds-worst-crimes-against-humanity/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，是2015年[[皮博迪獎|皮博迪獎]]、2015年AIB國際調查性紀錄片大獎獲獎紀錄片，記述[[諾貝爾和平獎|諾貝爾和平獎]]被提名人[[大衛·喬高|大衛·喬高]]和[[大衛·麥塔斯|大衛·麥塔斯]]對在[[中華人民共和國|中華人民共和國]]發生的[[對中共摘取法輪功學員及良心犯器官的指控|活摘器官及交易]]進行獨立調查的紀錄片。皮博迪獎評審評論「對錯綜複雜的器官交易及人體來源（human cost）提出強有力的證據，包括對被強迫參與活摘[[良心犯|良心犯]]器官的中國醫生進行訪談。這是對強摘器官移植的惡魔般系統（fiendish）的一項令人毛骨悚然（harrowing）揭露。」<ref>{{cite web|title=(Winner 2014)Human Harvest: China’s Illegal Organ Trade (International Syndication)|url=http://www.peabodyawards.com/award-profile/human-harvest-chinas-illegal-organ-trade|publisher=[[皮博迪獎|皮博迪獎]]官網|accessdate=2015-04-25|archive-date=2019-04-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190406181752/http://www.peabodyawards.com/award-profile/human-harvest-chinas-illegal-organ-trade|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Organ Harvesting Exposed at TEDx Talks: Two Davids & Goliath |url=https://fofg.org/multimedia/organ-harvesting-exposed-at-tedx-talks-two-davids-goliath/ |accessdate=2021-11-18 |work=Friends of Falun Gong |archive-date=2021-11-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211118033849/https://fofg.org/multimedia/organ-harvesting-exposed-at-tedx-talks-two-davids-goliath/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==製作==
電影由[[加拿大|加拿大]][[溫哥華|溫哥華]]華裔電影人李雲翔執導，2015年4月23日獲第74屆（2014年度）[[美國廣播電視文化成就獎|美國廣播電視文化成就獎]]（皮博迪獎）。李雲翔建議人們觀看紀錄片的證據與證人證詞，並作出自己的判斷<ref>{{cite news|author1=JESSICA KNEIPP|title=Why This Documentary ‘Human Harvest’ Just Won a Peabody Award|url=http://www.visiontimes.com/2015/04/24/why-this-documentary-human-harvest-just-won-a-peabody-award.html|agency=Vision Times|date=2015-04-24|accessdate=2015-04-25|archive-date=2020-10-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201024172011/https://visiontimes.com/2015/04/24/why-this-documentary-human-harvest-just-won-a-peabody-award.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=VSUN>{{cite news|author1=TIFFANY CRAWFORD,|title=Vancouver filmmaker wins prestigious Peabody Award for organ harvesting documentary|url=http://www.vancouversun.com/health/Vancouver+filmmaker+wins+prestigious+Peabody+Award+organ+harvesting+documentary/10998207/story.html#__federated=1|agency=VANCOUVER SUN [[溫哥華太陽報|溫哥華太陽報]]|quote=|date=2015-04-24|accessdate=2015-04-25|archive-date=2015-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150427221026/http://www.vancouversun.com/health/Vancouver+filmmaker+wins+prestigious+Peabody+Award+organ+harvesting+documentary/10998207/story.html#__federated=1|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name=CMF>{{cite news|title=Human Harvest Wins Prestigious Peabody Award|url=http://www.cmf-fmc.ca/press-room/article/2015/04/human-harvest-wins-prestigious-peabody-award/|publisher={{link-en|加拿大媒體基金會|Canada Media Fund}}|date=2015-04-23|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150425215710/http://www.cmf-fmc.ca/press-room/article/2015/04/human-harvest-wins-prestigious-peabody-award/|archivedate=2015-04-25}}</ref>。

==反响和评论==
2015年4月8日澳洲[[特別廣播服務公司|SBS]]公共電視台[[日界線_(澳洲SBS電視節目)|Dateline]]節目播放本片部分內容<ref name=SBS-0408>{{cite news|author1=SBS|title=Dateline: Human harvest - China’s organ trafficking|url=http://www.sbs.com.au/news/fragment/dateline-human-harvest-chinas-organ-trafficking|agency=[[特別廣播服務公司|SBS公共電視台]]|date=2015-04-08|accessdate=2015-04-25|archive-date=2019-12-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191207175926/https://www.sbs.com.au/news/fragment/dateline-human-harvest-chinas-organ-trafficking|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=SBS-0407>{{cite news|author1=Leon Lee|title=Human Harvest: China’s Organ Trafficking|url=http://www.sbs.com.au/news/dateline/story/human-harvest-chinas-organ-trafficking|agency=[[特別廣播服務公司|SBS澳洲特別廣播服務公司]]|date=2015-04-07|accessdate=2015-04-25|archive-date=2015-04-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150414141434/http://www.sbs.com.au/news/dateline/story/human-harvest-chinas-organ-trafficking|dead-url=yes}}</ref>，講述了器官交易、[[法輪功|法輪功]]學員遭受[[中國共產黨|中國共產黨]]政權[[群體滅絕|群體滅絕]]的情形，李雲翔在節目中透過[[推特|推特]]回答觀眾疑問<ref name=SBS-Audience>{{cite news|author1=Leon Lee|title=Human Harvest: Filmmaker Q&A（film）|url=http://www.sbs.com.au/news/dateline/article/2015/04/08/human-harvest-filmmaker-qa|agency=SBS|date=2015-04-08|accessdate=2015-04-25|archive-date=2015-04-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150414145839/http://www.sbs.com.au/news/dateline/article/2015/04/08/human-harvest-filmmaker-qa|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。<!--此處原有內容因無來源違反可供查證故進行移除-->

《[[每日郵報|每日郵報]]》報道，在器官捐赠率極低的中国，每年却有上萬起[[器官移植|器官移植]]手术，紀錄片揭露非法器官交易，而被盗取器官并杀害的主要对象是[[法轮功|法轮功]]学员。當李雲翔2006年第一次讀到[[對中共摘取法輪功學員及良心犯器官的指控|相關指控]]時，他不能相信，但幾個月後當《喬高-麥塔斯調查報告》發佈後，李受到啟發主動進一步調查，然而「要找到人們願意去談，要獲取他們的信任是一個緩慢的過程，製作這部影片歷時八年。」李指稱，目前中國每年非法器官交易額達十億美元。一些國家正制訂防止本國公民赴中國[[器官移植旅遊|器官移植旅遊]]（transplant tourism）的法律，以色列和西班牙已實施；美國國會、歐洲議會等國會已通過決議譴責並要求中共停止摘取良心犯器官<ref name=Dailymail>{{cite news|author1=JOHN CARNEY FOR (DAILY MAIL AUSTRALIA)|title=A Human Harvest: China’s organ trafficking exposed in shocking documentary that alleges the illegal trade is now worth a staggering US$1 billion a year（人體收割:曝光中國器官販運的驚人紀錄片指「每年非法器官交易額達10億美元」）|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3027088/A-Human-Harvest-Chinas-organ-trafficking-exposed-shocking-documentary-alleges-illegal-trade-worth-staggering-1-billion-year.html|agency=《[[每日郵報|每日郵報]]Daily Mail》|quote=中文編譯|date=2015-04-06|accessdate=2015-04-25|archive-date=2015-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150409003207/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3027088/A-Human-Harvest-Chinas-organ-trafficking-exposed-shocking-documentary-alleges-illegal-trade-worth-staggering-1-billion-year.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first1=Jayalakshmi K|title=China: Film exposes state sponsored organ harvesting from live prisoners|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/china-film-exposes-state-sponsored-organ-harvesting-live-prisoners-1495297|work=International Business Times英國《國際商業時報》|date=2015-04-08|accessdate=2015-05-03|archive-date=2015-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150412010522/http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/china-film-exposes-state-sponsored-organ-harvesting-live-prisoners-1495297|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

《[[悉尼晨锋报|悉尼晨锋报]]》指，电影揭露了中共的医院大规模非法盗取活著的法轮功学员器官，不施打[[麻醉|麻醉]]藥而取出器官高价出售。但中共官員否認這一指控，稱所用器官來自志願者。不過，參與調查的[[人權律師|人權律師]]們正努力將「該對活摘罪行負責的人」以[[反人類罪|反人類罪]]送上海牙[[國際刑事法院|國際刑事法院]]<ref name="SMT0408">{{cite news|author1=Kate Aubusson|title=China's gruesome live organ harvest exposed in documentary〈纪录片暴露中国可怕的活摘器官〉|url=http://www.smh.com.au/world/chinas-gruesome-live-organ-harvest-exposed-in-documentary-20150407-1mgabb.html|agency=《[[悉尼晨锋报|悉尼晨锋报]]The Sydney Morning Herald》|date=2015-04-08|accessdate=2015-04-25|archive-date=2015-04-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150411025500/http://www.smh.com.au/world/chinas-gruesome-live-organ-harvest-exposed-in-documentary-20150407-1mgabb.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

《[[澳洲新聞集團|澳洲新聞集團]]網》的報道〈中国另一大事-活体摘取器官〉指出「这是一个犹如恐怖电影中的故事，但却在这十多年来普遍发生在中国。政府所属的医院秘密地从成千上万的囚犯身上盗取器官，當他们还活着時摘取其器官。」导演李云翔及片中的调查员们都在试图结束这惨无人道的非法器官交易产业；報道指出「看似这每年十億美元的产业即将消亡，但对于在这场可恶的罪行中受害的人们却为时已晚。」<ref name=NEWSAU>{{cite news|title=China’s other big business: Harvesting organs from prisoners when they’re still alive〈中国另一大事——活体摘取器官〉|url=http://www.news.com.au/entertainment/tv/chinas-other-big-business-harvesting-organs-from-prisoners-when-theyre-still-alive/story-e6frfmyi-1227294577229|agency=News.com.au（澳洲新聞集團網）|date=2015-04-08|accessdate=2015-04-25|archive-date=2015-04-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150410010315/http://www.news.com.au/entertainment/tv/chinas-other-big-business-harvesting-organs-from-prisoners-when-theyre-still-alive/story-e6frfmyi-1227294577229|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

大衛‧喬高在《[[新西蘭國家廣播電台|新西蘭國家廣播電台]]》專訪指出，中共的器官活摘交易每年獲利10億美元，對於面臨財政困難的中國衛生系統而言是筆巨額收入。<ref>{{cite news|title=David Kilgour - Forced Organ Harvesting（節目錄音）|url=http://www.radionz.co.nz/national/programmes/sunday/audio/201754689/david-kilgour-forced-organ-harvesting|accessdate=2015-05-17|agency=Radio NZ [[新西蘭國家廣播電台|新西蘭國家廣播電台]]|quote=|archive-date=2015-05-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150526003216/http://www.radionz.co.nz/national/programmes/sunday/audio/201754689/david-kilgour-forced-organ-harvesting|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

[[加拿大|加拿大]]前亚太[[国务卿|国务卿]]{{dn|date=6月 2022}}[[大卫·乔高|大卫·乔高]]和[[人权|人权]]律师[[大卫·麦塔斯|大卫·麦塔斯]]，以及美国记者[[伊森·葛特曼|伊森·葛特曼]]出的新报告，AN UPDATE TO ‘[[BLOODY_HARVEST|BLOODY HARVEST]]’ & ‘[[THE_SLAUGHTER|THE SLAUGHTER]]’<ref>AN UPDATE TO ‘BLOODY HARVEST’ & ‘THE SLAUGHTER’,[http://endorganpillaging.org/an-update/]</ref>，报告中说，从[[中共|中共]]系统公开的那些数据分析，包括：每年的手术量、移植医院的数字、有关证人证词、移植的床位、对抓捕的[[法轮功|法轮功]]学员大面积的验血等。得出的结论是[[器官移植|器官移植]]手术数量基本超过10万一年，可能是11万一年。

